“We want our sound to go into the soul of the audience, and see if it can awaken some little thing in their minds... Cause there are so many sleeping people.” - Jimi Hendrix I try to keep my posts "good vibe zones". So, instead of finding the one thing in here you don't like and commenting only on that, also comment about something you DID like. Balance the negativity. Love you long time. So, I made a discord server. It's a relaxed environment where you can take/donate memes to the cause, play trivia twice a week, chat about lots of topics or about nothing at all. We also have Jack Box game night and are setting up movie night! Very laid back/relaxed vibe. item.title: I made a stained glass Thing. I love lamp.
item.description:
Track is "Hammond Song" by The Roches
Fra-GEE-lay: it must be Italian
This took me about ten months to get it right. The bodice is roughly 27 pounds of cathedral glass, solder, and steel. I wired both the pendant lamp and the standing lamp myself, and added dimmable LED bulbs with heart-shaped filaments. It was a real bitch to keep each solder seam level, and I had to replace several panels that I broke in the process, but it was all worth it.
Behold! The soft glow of electric sex, gleaming in the window. https://www.instagram.com/gracie_rowboat
